  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2022.08.1-alpha-7dabdc32`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: `Debian GNU/Linux 11 (bullseye)`\r\n\r\nCommit hash : `7dabdc32`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nErigon, as an EL layer to be used with a CL has a [paragraph](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon#beacon-chain-consensus-layer) in the readme page.\r\nThis ¬ß explain how to run erigon in pruned mode, and working with a beacon chain (without specifying the network)\r\nCurrently, the recommandation is the following parameters :\r\n- `--prune=htc --prune.r.before=<old block number>`\r\n\r\nand a pruned instance of erigon with rights parameters should be used as an EL with a CL.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nbut for a long time, in the README.md the recommandation was the following parameters:\r\n- `--prune=htc --prune.r.before=11184524`\r\n\r\nWe can see the change in this commit\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/commit/7199dcf7a2826da5dd9d30bc9e24860edb4de2eb#diff-b335630551682c19a781afebcf4d07bf978fb1f8ac04c6bf87428ed5106870f5L181.\r\n\r\nFrom my mind, it's ok to make generic this kind of parameter, but the issue is that **the previous block number noticed 11184524 was wrong** ‚ùå   !\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nOn the mainnet, the deposit contract is created on the block **11052984** ‚úîÔ∏è [etherscan link](https://etherscan.io/tx/0xe75fb554e433e03763a1560646ee22dcb74e5274b34c5ad644e7c0f619a7e1d0)\r\n\r\nSo i dont know why the block number was **11184524** ‚ùå before in the documentation, but if erigon prune receipts between the real contract creation block **11052984** <  **pruned receipts** < **11184524**. It could have some strange behaviours I suppose because there are missing receipts from the contract creation.\r\n\r\n#### Question :question:\r\nShould we resync all started instances with the wrong block number ?\r\n\r\n#### Communication üó£Ô∏è\r\n_I think we should communicate to all stakers who had started in prune mode, with this wrong block number, if a resync is needed._\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nstart an instance with  `--prune=htc --prune.r.before=11184524`\r\n\r\n\r\n",
